Feature idealist:
	settings changed vimstyle ":option"

	option for border / borderless
	option for coordinates / coordinateless
	configurable margins [left-margin, top-margin, left-right-centered, top-bottom-centered, both-centered]
	configurable keybindings
	configurable flagsymbol, bombsymbol, emptysymbol, etc.	
	hjkl move, f=flag, s=step(step onto spot)
	
	option to autoreaveal all empty spaces by 0-mine blocks
	option to type coordinates
	double-clicker (detonate all in radius, not flagged)
	native-solver

	timer?
		display timer,
		hide timer and report when game is finished
		bomb-timer: end game when max_time reached

	option for interact-time / pregame randomization [guarentee player does not immediately click on a bomb by ensuring first click is not a bomb, or true-random?]
	option for no-ambiguous-mode [is it possible to make a truly logical minesweeper, where the player can always solve the board?]

	hotkey to reset
	hotkey to lock reset-hotkey	

	setting for height & width
	setting for # bombs
	setting for bomb percentage (overrides #-bomb setting: rather than setting # bombs for every )
	
	setting-packages
		user-saved difficulties

	option to save times / highscores / streaks [game-record]

maybe that's all I can think of today... if I come up with more ideas for options, will I write them in a daily log and add them to a seperate masterfile, or will I just append them to this [above] list?
I guess we'll see!
